  "prompt": "What is Inc company?",
  "response": "\"Inc.\" is an abbreviation for \"Incorporated.\" It is used in the names of corporations or companies to indicate that the business is a legal corporation. In legal terms, incorporation is the process by which a new or existing business registers as a corporation. This process provides the corporation with a separate legal identity from its owners, meaning that the corporation can own assets, incur liabilities, and be involved in legal proceedings distinct from its shareholders. Incorporation also often provides limited liability protection to its shareholders, meaning they are not personally liable for the corporation\u2019s debts beyond their investment in the company.",
